Interface Map<K,V>

    K - Key
    V - Value
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<Entry<K,V>>, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMap, AVLTree, BinarySearchTree, HashMap, OrderedLinkedMap

extends Collection<Entry<K,V>>
    Author:

      boolean containsKey(K key)
      Verifies if Map contains given key

      If there is an entry in the dictionary whose key is the specified key, returns its value; otherwise, returns null.

      Returns a collection with map keys

      Returns an iterator of the map's keys
      V put(K key, V value)
      If there is an entry in the dictionary whose key is the specified key, replaces its value by the specified value and returns the old value; otherwise, inserts the entry (key, value) and returns null.
      V remove(K key)
      If there is an entry in the dictionary whose key is the specified key, removes it from the dictionary and returns its value; otherwise, returns null.

      Returns a collection with map values
